§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given a nonempty set $A ⊂ 𝗥^d$, the ❬polar❭ (or ❬polar
    set❭) of $A$ is the set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set{c ∈ 𝗥^d}{c^⊤x ≤ 1 \quad \text{for all } x ∈ A} ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the polar of the set $A$ by $A^∘$. ⦉
⦉

